# 03 - Cyber Kill Chain

## What I Learned
- The 7 stages of the Cyber Kill Chain model developed by Lockheed Martin
- How attackers move from initial reconnaissance to final objective
- Purpose and techniques used in each stage:
  - Reconnaissance
  - Weaponization
  - Delivery
  - Exploitation
  - Installation
  - Command and Control (C2)
  - Actions on Objectives

## Key Takeaways
- Understood the full attack lifecycle
- Learned how to map real-world attacks to different Kill Chain stages
- Realized how SOC teams can break the kill chain at different stages


## Tools / Concepts Covered
- Cyber Kill Chain Framework
- Attack Lifecycle
- Defensive Strategies at each stage
